The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 The Tata Coffee board has recommended a 65 per cent dividend for its shareholders for 2004-05 encouraged by a 77 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 30.18 crore. The revenues of the company during the fiscal grew by 13 per cent at Rs 201.66 crore from Rs 179.03 crore in 2003-04. The earning per share improved significantly to Rs 24.21 from Rs 13.72. The company has recently acquired Highhill Coffee India, a 100 per cent export-oriented unit producing soluble coffee, which is in the process of being merged. 

 Dabur Foods is setting up its first state-of-the-art packaging facility in Rajasthan at an investment of Rs 17 crore. The new plant will help the Rs 130-crore company catering to the northern and western markets. The two regions together contribute more than 40 per cent of the total sales of the company.

 The Liberty Shoes board has recommended a 60 per cent dividend to its shareholders for 2004-05, encouraged by a 19 per cent rise in net profits at Rs 9.80 crore over the previous year?s figure. However, the sales of the company for the fiscal marginally declined to Rs 194.80 crore from Rs 199 crore in 2003-04.

 REI Agro has recommended a 15 per cent dividend for its shareholders for 2004-05 on the back of a 140 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 37.85 crore from Rs 15.80 crore in the previous fiscal. The rice processing company has posted a 40 per cent increase in sales at Rs 845.02 crore compared with Rs 602.90 crore in 2003-04. 

 Mukand Ltd has posted a higher net profit for 2004-05 at Rs 185.72 crore from Rs 12.92 crore in 2003-04. The net sales of the company during the fiscal grew to Rs 1,523.86 crore from Rs 11070.68 crore in the previous year. 

 Ramco Systems Ltd has got the Gold Certified status in the Microsoft Partner Programme for its competency in independent software vendor and advanced infrastructure solutions. Microsoft Gold Certified partners receive rich benefits, such as access, training and support, which give them a competitive advantage in the marketplace.

 Sun Microsystems has kicked off a new branding campaign. The campaign presents the power of sharing and collaboration in action, featuring Sun customers and illustrating the solutions, which the companies have created together. 

 Rajesh Exports Ltd has bagged a Rs 226-crore export order from the US-based MR Gems for 22-carat designer jewellery. Under the contract, the order has to be executed within five months, the company has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

